                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1775" notAfter="1804">
                        <p>Probably rebound in the <placeName
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208" key="place_7000208"
                              >Indian subcontinent</placeName> in a hybrid British-Indian style,
                           possibly for former <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/79255120"
                              key="person_79255120">Henry George Keene</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Resewn on two recessed cord supports, laced into pasteboards. Edges
                           trimmed, spattered pale gray, and decorative front-bead endbands sewn at
                           at <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and <locus from="Tail"
                              to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covered in full smooth-grained maroon goatskin
                              <material>leather</material>.</p>
                        <decoNote>Boards diced on the exteriors, with the margins repeatedly stamped
                           with a rosette in blind. Spine panels divided with single fillet lines in
                           gold, with a green leather label titled:<lb/>
                           <q xml:lang="en">LIFE OF<lb/> CHRIST IN<lb/> PERSIAN</q>.</decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>244</height>
                              <width>149</width>
                              <depth>42</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                        <condition>Handle binding with caution. In fair but stable condition, with
                           the upper headcap torn and headband broken. </condition>
                     </binding>
